<html t:type="layout" xmlns:p="tapestry:parameter"
      xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_3.xsd">
    
    <h1>Direct transfer ready</h1>  
    
    <p> The files you uploaded are now ready to be transferred to another person or system. Use one of
        the three options below to complete the transfer. </p>
    
    <h2>Send to recipient</h2>
    
    <p> To ensure the security of the files you are sending, you need to communicate the following 
        via two different communication mediums. This is to reduce the chance of a malicious third party intercepting
        both the link and key.
    </p>
    
    <form>
    	<div class="field">
	    	<label><em>Unlock link</em>: send via e-mail</label>
	    	<input type="text" class="link" value="${unlockLink}" />
    	</div>
    	<div class="field">
    		<label><em>Unlock code</em>: communicate via SMS or phone</label>
    		<input type="text" class="code" value="${transfer.code}" />
    	</div>
    </form>
    
    <t:if test="!transfer.agreement">
        <h2>Direct link</h2>
        
        <p> A direct link is for situations where you simply want to transfer the file(s) to another system and can either
            copy the following link, or type it out again (note that the file name part is not required). </p>
        
        <form>
        	<div class="field">
    	    	<label>Copy to remote system</label>
    	    	<input type="text" class="link direct" value="${directLink}" />
        	</div>
        </form>
        
        
        <h2>Send to mobile (scannable QR code)</h2>
        
        <p> Scan the following image with your mobile phone. </p>
    
    	<div class="field">
        	<label>QR code</label>
        	<img src="${qrCodeImageLink}" alt="QR code for mobile transfer" class="qrcode"/>
    	</div>
    </t:if>
</html>
